  Training/test split: True
  Instructions: Participants were instructed to focus their gaze on the designated object for 2 s before initiating the reach-and-grasp action. Once they completed the grasp, they held the object for at least 1–2 s. When they returned their hand to the starting position, a small insert on a screen showed them the number of grasps they had already performed on the designated object. Participants paused at least for 4 s before starting a new trial (inter trial interval).

